name: New release

name: New release
body:
A lot of updates/fixes/major improvements.
The code now supports not only pure-python ciphers but pycryptodome as well which makes it much faster (especially for smb3)
Added better registry API and improved event6 among many other things.
A lot of new scanner types have been introduced as well as "smbget" to download files and "smbreg" to read registry remotely

Important notice: if you want the speed improvements then you will have to install pycryptodome separately, and also you can't use the compiled windows versions because of limitations in pyInstaller.
Binaries were compiled with pyInstalled on Win10x64

name: First release
body:
First release of the asynchronous smb client for windows.
Executable was created with pyinstaller on Windows 10 x64
